Privacy Policy for Bouncy Bird
===============================

Effective date: 19th March, 2023

Welcome to Bouncy Bird, a mobile game designed for children under the age of 13. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and disclose personal information from users of our game.

Information We Collect
----------------------
We collect the following types of personal information from users of our game:

Device information: We may collect information about the device you use to access our game, such as the device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.

Usage information: We may collect information about how you use our game, such as which levels you complete, how much time you spend playing the game, and your high scores.

Personal information: We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us, such as your name and email address. We do not require users to provide this information in order to use our game.

Use of Information
------------------
We use the personal information we collect to:

Provide and improve our game: We use the information we collect to operate, maintain, and improve our game, and to develop new features and content.

Personalize the game experience: We may use the information we collect to customize the game experience for individual users, such as by recommending levels or challenges based on the user's past activity.

Communicate with users: We may use the personal information we collect to communicate with users about the game, such as by sending updates or notifications about new features or content.

Disclosure of Information
-------------------------
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer users' personal information to third parties. We may disclose personal information in the following circumstances:

To service providers: We may share personal information with service providers who help us operate our game, such as hosting providers, data analytics providers, and customer support providers.

To comply with the law: We may disclose personal information if required by law, such as in response to a court order or subpoena.

In the event of a sale or merger: If we sell or transfer all or a portion of our business, we may transfer personal information to the new owner or successor.

Security of Information
-----------------------
We take reasonable measures to protect the personal information we collect from unauthorized access, disclosure, and alteration. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your personal information.

Children's Privacy
------------------
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13 without verifiable parental consent. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under the age of 13 without parental consent, we will take steps to remove that information from our servers.

Contact Us
----------
If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or our practices with respect to personal information, please contact us at [hiten247@gmail.com].

Changes to Privacy Policy
-------------------------
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make material changes to our Privacy Policy, we will notify you by email or by posting a notice in the game. Your continued use of the game after the effective date of the updated Privacy Policy constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.

.END
